Class JmxPolicy

  • net.corda.testing.driver.JmxPolicy

      • JmxPolicy

        public JmxPolicy(boolean startJmxHttpServer,
                 PortAllocation jmxHttpServerPortAllocation)
        Deprecated. 

        A class containing configuration information for Jolokia JMX, to be used when creating a node via the Driver.driver.

        Parameters:
        startJmxHttpServer - Indicates whether the spawned nodes should start with a Jolokia JMX agent to enable remoteJMX monitoring using HTTP/JSON.
        jmxHttpServerPortAllocation - The port allocation strategy to use for remote Jolokia/JMX monitoring over HTTP.Defaults to incremental from port 7005. Use NodeHandle.getJmxAddress to get the assigned address.
        See Also:
        Driver.driver
